# LeTARA – Django Web Application

LeTARA is a Django-based web application that provides:
- A home dashboard
- A profile page
- Camera capture via browser
- Image upload with a processing pipeline

This README explains **how to run the website locally** using Django.

---

## 📦 Requirements

Make sure you have the following installed:

- **Python 3.10+**
- **pip** (comes with Python)
- **Virtual environment support** (recommended)

Check installation:
```bat
python --version
pip --version

letara/
├── letara/          # Django project settings
├── app/             # Main Django app
├── data/            # Uploaded, processed, and captured images
├── manage.py
└── README.md

=================================================================================

🚀 How to Run the Website (Windows CMD)
1️⃣ Open Command Prompt

Navigate to the project root (where manage.py is):

cd path\to\letara

2️⃣ (Optional but Recommended) Activate Virtual Environment

If you already created a virtual environment:

venv\Scripts\activate


You should see (venv) in the terminal.

If you don’t have one yet:

python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate

3️⃣ Install Dependencies
pip install django pillow


(Install other dependencies here if your pipeline requires them.)

4️⃣ Run the Django Development Server
python manage.py runserver


If successful, you will see:

Starting development server at http://127.0.0.1:8000/

5️⃣ Open the Website in Your Browser 🌐

Visit:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/

